    "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds a leading emoji to each option in the `recall_dispatch_*` triage menu (\ud83e\udd16 keep AFK, \ud83d\udc64 keep human, \u2702\ufe0f split, \ud83d\udce6 rehome, \ud83d\udc6f dedup, \ud83d\uddd1\ufe0f stale close, \u23ed\ufe0f defer).\n- Updates the wire-token list in `TRIAGE_DESCRIPTION` to match, so the schema description and the user-facing menu stay aligned.\n- Notes in the prompt that Kai may now answer by emoji as well as by name or ordinal.\n\nThe menu lives in `src/display/mcp/dispatch.rs` (`TRIAGE_MENU_HUMAN` and `TRIAGE_DESCRIPTION`). No behavior change \u2014 the wire enum and routing logic are untouched.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [ ] `coily ci` clean locally\n- [ ] Kick off `recall_dispatch_begin` in a real session and confirm the rendered triage menu shows the emojis\n- [ ] Confirm answering by emoji still resolves to the correct wire token (model-level behavior; no parser change required)\n\n---\n_Generated by [Claude Code](https://claude.ai/code/session_016ZYnyXeyuaPN2QcK8CSkLL)_",
